# Subgroup Analysis: High-Risk Patients

**Enhanced benefits in challenging patient populations**

::: warning
**High-Risk Subgroups:**
- Patients with multiple prior CTs (>3)
- Active smokers >40 pack-years
- Family history of lung cancer
- Previous lung nodules detected
:::

| Risk Group | Control Accuracy | AI-Assisted | Improvement |
|------------|------------------|-------------|-------------|
| **Multiple CTs** | 79.3% | 91.8% | +12.5% |
| **Heavy Smokers** | 81.2% | 94.1% | +12.9% |
| **Family History** | 83.1% | 95.2% | +12.1% |
| **Prior Nodules** | 77.8% | 89.9% | +12.1% |

@notes:
- High-risk patients most challenging diagnostically
- AI particularly helpful in complex cases
- Consistent improvement across risk factors
- Clinical impact greatest where needed most

